<br>
This is what would have saved that server: experience loss for ganking/assisting in ganking greenies outside of a certain level range (say, similar to the other PVP servers). There would have been no incentive for the power gaming rush to the top and the subsequent griefing, since levels are what make or break on SZ. Sure, you could run around killing greenies, but you would lose a whole lotta exp doing it. There has to be a consequence to griefing, and on SZ there is no consequence. <br>
<br>
It's too bad it failed. PvP can be great. One of my best experiences was rushing down to South Antonica on VZ to hunt the named cyclops in the Rathe mountains for my ivy etched tunic. I was on the edge of my seat the whole time waiting to run into darkies since it was deep behind enemy lines. Had a couple occurrences, but got clear. <br>
<br>
Oh well, having fun on FV anyway.<br>
<br>
Highgate<br>
